<subSubSection pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,1302,1975]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1374,1399]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Idiosoma large in size (&gt; length 
<quantity box="[690,791,1374,1399]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="1300.0">1300 µm</quantity>
) and roundish (dorsal shield L/W ratio 1.2); gnathosomal bay deep, narrow Y-shaped; medial margin of Cx-II/III relatively long; genital field anteriorly enlarged, laterally straight, tapering posteriorly; ejaculatory complex normal in shape (
<figureCitation box="[910,1019,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1662,1684]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1641]" captionTargetId="figure-210@42.[151,1436,193,1641]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 30A–M. Photographs of ejaculatory complex. A Monatractides longiventris (K. Viets, 1939), Mahua stream. B M. oxystomus (K. Viets, 1935), Kipungit River. C–D M. cf. macroporus (K. Viets, 1935): C = stream Bansadon Trail; D = Little Lumotok stream. E–F M. epiales n. sp., Kipungit River: E = holotype; F = paratype. G M. phantasos n. sp., Great Lumotok stream. H M. phobetor n. sp., Little Lumotok stream. I–L M. morpheus n. sp. I = holotype, small stream Layang Layang; K = Kemantis stream; K = Little Lumotok stream. M M. heracles n. sp., Little Lumotok stream." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927975" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927975/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 30M</figureCitation>
); palp with thick, pennate setae on P2 and P-3, distal margin of P-2, P-3 and P-4 medially with several pointed extensions; ventral setae on P-4 thickened and short.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="61" lastPageNumber="62" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,1302,1975]" box="[151,289,1554,1579]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,1554,1579]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,1302,1975]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
Male. 
<emphasis box="[270,457,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">General features</emphasis>
—Idiosoma large in size and roundish; frontal plates broad (L/W ratio 1.8), shorter than shoulder plates (shoulder/frontal plate L ratio 1.16–1.2); frontal margin medially slightly convex between flat, anterolaterally directed protrusions (
<figureCitation box="[567,675,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1082,1104]" captionTargetBox="[153,1429,196,1053]" captionTargetId="figure-384@61.[151,1436,193,1061]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 37A–C. Monatractides heracles n. sp., holotype male, Little Lumotok stream: A = frontal margin of idiosoma, dorsal view; B = dorsal shield; C = idiosoma, ventral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927992/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 37A</figureCitation>
); Cxgl–4 located far anteriorly, near tips of Cx-I; the tips of Cx-I orientated to the lateral side, gnathosomal bay deep, narrow Y-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[993,1101,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1082,1104]" captionTargetBox="[153,1429,196,1053]" captionTargetId="figure-384@61.[151,1436,193,1061]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 37A–C. Monatractides heracles n. sp., holotype male, Little Lumotok stream: A = frontal margin of idiosoma, dorsal view; B = dorsal shield; C = idiosoma, ventral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927992/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 37C</figureCitation>
); medial margin of Cx-II/III relatively long; genital field anteriorly enlarged, laterally straight, tapering posteriorly; ejaculatory complex (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1662,1684]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1641]" captionTargetId="figure-210@42.[151,1436,193,1641]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 30A–M. Photographs of ejaculatory complex. A Monatractides longiventris (K. Viets, 1939), Mahua stream. B M. oxystomus (K. Viets, 1935), Kipungit River. C–D M. cf. macroporus (K. Viets, 1935): C = stream Bansadon Trail; D = Little Lumotok stream. E–F M. epiales n. sp., Kipungit River: E = holotype; F = paratype. G M. phantasos n. sp., Great Lumotok stream. H M. phobetor n. sp., Little Lumotok stream. I–L M. morpheus n. sp. I = holotype, small stream Layang Layang; K = Kemantis stream; K = Little Lumotok stream. M M. heracles n. sp., Little Lumotok stream." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927975" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927975/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 30M</figureCitation>
) normal in shape (proximal and distal arms and proximal chamber well developed); posterior suture line of Cx-IV distinct, extending posteriorly beyond posterior margin of genital field, medially approaching and parallel to each other; line of primary sclerotization close to posterior margin of genital field; excretory pore and Vgl–2 well separated from the line of primary sclerotization, Vgl–2 posterior to excretory pore; gnathosomal rostrum truncated (
<figureCitation box="[159,264,1914,1939]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="62.[151,250,1569,1591]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,203,1536]" captionTargetId="figure-154@62.[151,1436,195,1547]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 38A–D. Monatractides heracles n. sp., holotype male, Little Lumotok stream: A = palp, medial view; B = palp, lateral view (P-5 lacking); C = I-L-5 and -6; D = gnathosoma. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927994" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927994/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 38D</figureCitation>
); palp with thick, pennate setae on P-2 and P-3, distal margin of P-2, P-3 and P-4 medially with several pointed extensions (
<figureCitation box="[375,524,1950,1975]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="62.[151,250,1569,1591]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,203,1536]" captionTargetId="figure-154@62.[151,1436,195,1547]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 38A–D. Monatractides heracles n. sp., holotype male, Little Lumotok stream: A = palp, medial view; B = palp, lateral view (P-5 lacking); C = I-L-5 and -6; D = gnathosoma. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927994" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927994/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Figs. 38A–B</figureCitation>
); ventral setae on P-4 short, not reaching the tip of P-5.
</paragraph>
