<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1436,1174,1919]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,1642,1667]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Discussion</emphasis>
. The male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pešić &amp; Smit, 2014" authorityName="Pešić &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2014" box="[497,766,1642,1667]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heracles" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[497,766,1642,1667]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Monatractides heracles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[776,843,1642,1667]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[776,836,1642,1667]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">n. sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is easily distinguished from other members of the genus due to the combination of a large idiosoma dimensions (&gt; length 
<quantity box="[1031,1138,1678,1703]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="1300.0">1300 µm</quantity>
) and a narrow Y-shaped gnathosomal bay. Further diagnostic features of the new species include the relatively long medial suture line of Cx-II+III, posterior suture line of Cx-IV extending beyond posterior margin of genital field and medially approaching to each other, and by the shape of the palp with thick, pennate setae on P-2 and P-3, distal margin of P2 and P-3 medially with several pointed extensions and a thickened and short ventral setae on P-4.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1436,1174,1919]" box="[199,819,1858,1883]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1858,1883]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Habitat.</emphasis>
Sandy/bouldery stream, shaded by rain forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,853,1894,1919]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1436,1174,1919]" box="[199,853,1894,1919]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1894,1919]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Distribution.</emphasis>
Borneo; known only from the locus typicus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
